if what I saw was real.

25
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:16,670
 The Witch's Diner 
 EP. 05 Yeonbunmali noodles that tie bonds. 
 (TN: Yeonbunmali – year-end festive noodle dish.)

26
00:02:16,670 --> 00:02:19,090
Here's your food.

27
00:02:22,140 --> 00:02:24,760
Bon Appetit.

28
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:27,640
This isn't even your open time, but you opened the shop for us. Thank you very much.

29
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:30,710
Of course I should, considering the person who asked me.

30
00:02:30,710 --> 00:02:32,750
A gift for Min Ju.

31
00:02:32,750 --> 00:02:36,370
Thanks, and why do you give her something every time you come?

32
00:02:36,370 --> 00:02:37,420
I'm envious.

33
00:02:37,420 --> 00:02:40,470
You can also just get married.

34
00:02:42,250 --> 00:02:46,130
This guy suddenly desperately asked me a favor.

35
00:02:46,130 --> 00:02:47,950
I wondered why he was doing that.

36
00:02:47,950 --> 00:02:50,440
I think I did well by opening up early.

37
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,070
Bon Appetit.

38
00:02:52,070 --> 00:02:54,800
- Thank you for the food, Hyung. 
 - Sure thing.

39
00:02:57,150 --> 00:02:58,880
Eat up.

40
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:02,050
- Yes. Thank you for the food. 
 - Of course.

41
00:03:20,370 --> 00:03:22,210
Are you uncomfortable?

42
00:03:22,210 --> 00:03:24,440
What? Oh, no.

43
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:27,000
No, I'm alright.

44
00:03:30,870 --> 00:03:33,330
Shall we take a break before continuing?

45
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:36,180
Sure.

46
00:03:42,370 --> 00:03:43,330
Here.

47
00:03:43,330 --> 00:03:45,290
Thank you.

48
00:03:45,290 --> 00:03:50,420
Ah, right. We met so that I could return the fountain pen, but I almost forgot about it.

49
00:03:50,420 --> 00:03:51,600
Thank you.

50
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:54,610
You were uncomfortable because I asked to meet out of the blue, right?

51
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:59,140
No. I had to return this to you anyway. Returning it soon is better.

52
00:03:59,140 --> 00:04:00,950
Here.

53
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:16,860
This might seem unusual, but I always carry this pen wherever I go.

54
00:04:16,860 --> 00:04:19,120
Like a talisman.

55
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:22,630
Oh. Yes.

56
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:26,120
Since you're a writer, a pen might be precious.

57
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:28,590
I didn't think it was unusual.

58
00:04:28,590 --> 00:04:31,100
Rather than that,

59
00:04:32,540 --> 00:04:35,730
- my mother gave it to me as a gift. 
 - Oh.

60
00:04:36,610 --> 00:04:40,250
My mother raised me alone with great difficulty.

61
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:42,750
I couldn't even dream of being a writer.

62
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:46,210
There wasn't a job I wouldn't do to make money.

63
00:04:46,210 --> 00:04:50,240
One day, my mother gifted me this pen.

64
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:52,360
She told me to do what I wanted to.

65
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:57,340
 You can get a job slowly. I'll be responsible for you.

66
00:04:57,340 --> 00:05:00,550
So I poured my life into this work.

67
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:04,570
I wanted to be filial to her once I was doing well.

68
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:07,380
But she didn't wait for me.

69
00:05:09,930 --> 00:05:12,430
Oh, sorry. I talked too much about myself.

70
00:05:13,290 --> 00:05:17,790
Your mother would be proud of you.

71
00:05:17,790 --> 00:05:21,100
Because you have become such a famous writer.

72
00:05:27,170 --> 00:05:33,400
I actually gathered up my courage.

73
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:36,050
What?

74
00:05:36,050 --> 00:05:39,400
I wanted to see you, Jin

75
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:45,210
It might seem like an excuse but I think that your taking this pen

76
00:05:45,210 --> 00:05:47,190
felt like destiny to me.

77
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:49,610
 If you are fated to meet, even if you don't force it,

78
00:05:49,610 --> 00:05:51,780
 you will meet.

79
00:05:54,630 --> 00:05:57,420
Here is my house.

80
00:05:57,420 --> 00:05:59,550
I had fun today. Thank you.

81
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:01,980
Yes, thank you too.

82
00:06:01,980 --> 00:06:04,580
- I'll call you. 
 - Sure.

83
00:06:06,920 --> 00:06:09,220
 It is inevitable,

84
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:12,010
 because it is a pre-determined sequence of events.

85
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,900
There could be a solution that's good for everyone—

86
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:17,970
There is no such solution that's good for everyone.

87
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:24,370
Hello.

88
00:06:25,460 --> 00:06:26,980
Today is a day off.

89
00:06:26,980 --> 00:06:28,440
I just came.

90
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,920
Noona Jin didn't come, right?

91
00:06:33,060 --> 00:06:35,150
Hi, part-timer student.

92
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:39,820
Could you talk to me for a moment?

93
00:06:49,670 --> 00:06:52,250
You should have a drink too.

94
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:53,440
I'm still a student.

95
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:55,580
You are twenty years old.

96
00:07:15,420 --> 00:07:20,760
I actually made plans to watch a movie with Noona Jin.

97
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,850
So you got stood up.

98
00:07:22,850 --> 00:07:27,520
You can't get used to it no matter how many times it happens.

99
00:07:28,530 --> 00:07:31,000
You will need practice.

100
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:35,150
Practice getting hurt and practice being numb to it.

101
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:41,500
All I hoped for was to eat together and watch movies. That was all.

102
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,940
Don't be too greedy.

103
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:48,400
The more you desire her, the harder it gets.

104
00:07:58,700 --> 00:08:00,890
It's as dark as midnight here.

105
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:03,960
Aigoo, you rotten, lazy boy!

106
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:08,030
Get up. Get up! Oh my goodness.

107
00:08:08,030 --> 00:08:11,100
You are fifty years old now, but

108
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:14,880
you still can't take off your socks properly.

109
00:08:16,190 --> 00:08:19,080
What now? What happened this time to make you so foul-tempered?

110
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:23,020
Have I ever nagged you to get married or make food for me?

111
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:26,990
All I want you to do is live like a human being. Is that too greedy?

112
00:08:26,990 --> 00:08:30,800
Oh my goodness, my mother's vocal cords are healthy.

113
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,960
Where are you going when your mother is talking?

114
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,350
I'm so frustrated.

115
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,190
Father.

116
00:08:49,190 --> 00:08:54,080
Do you think you will be unhappy if I don't go to college?

117
00:08:55,590 --> 00:09:00,090
I would just worry.

118
00:09:00,090 --> 00:09:02,800
"What if he has it as hard as me?"

119
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:09,180
I would want you to be happy just as others are.

120
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:15,200
Did you drop out of track and field?

121
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:20,780
Sorry. I was going to tell you.

122
00:09:20,780 --> 00:09:27,350
I got confused if I was doing it because I liked it or because that was all I could do.

123
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:36,990
If you were the one who decided it, then I'm okay.

124
00:09:36,990 --> 00:09:38,850
There is no answer to life.

125
00:09:38,850 --> 00:09:41,130
You don't have to live up to our expectations.

126
00:09:41,130 --> 00:09:45,790
I think that your decision is the most important.

127
00:09:49,570 --> 00:09:51,510
Let's eat quickly.

128
00:09:51,510 --> 00:09:53,150
Yes.

129
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:05,450
 I actually gathered up my courage.

130
00:10:05,450 --> 00:10:08,610
 I wanted to see you, Jin.

131
00:10:15,660 --> 00:10:18,090
- Hi, Yun Mi. 
 - So what did you guys do when you met?

132
00:10:18,090 --> 00:10:20,680
 Just... What's there to talk about?

133
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:23,330
What? You're making me more curious.

134
00:10:23,330 --> 00:10:28,200
Tom Kim... our lifestyle is quite different from his, no?

135
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,940
That's right. He's half celebrity and he's older too.

136
00:10:30,940 --> 00:10:33,750
But... I think we're quite similar too.

137
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:36,590
He's surprisingly average and modest.

138
00:10:36,590 --> 00:10:38,460
Eh? What are you saying?

139
00:10:38,460 --> 00:10:41,190
Is he the same or is he different?

140
00:10:41,190 --> 00:10:45,760
He was raised by a single mother and suffered a lot too.

141
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:49,680
But he talks about it as if it were nothing.

142
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:53,330
 What's this, Jeong Jin? You've already fallen for him?

143
00:10:57,050 --> 00:11:00,370
Hey! Hey, I'll call you later, okay?

144
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,510
Hello.

145
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:11,000
 Did you sleep well? What are you doing today?

146
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:14,150
I'm just going to work today.

147
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:29,120
Hyung, did you hand in a resignation letter?

148
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,310
Yes.

149
00:11:30,310 --> 00:11:34,960
Honestly, it was hard to keep up with class while doing sports.

150
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:39,000
Slowly, slowly, I'm going to start again from the basics.

151
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,850
Call me.

152
00:11:44,850 --> 00:11:46,960
That's right.

153
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:48,770
Okay.

154
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:53,750
Don't work too hard.

155
00:11:56,370 --> 00:11:58,490
What did you say?

156
00:11:58,490 --> 00:12:02,250
You act tough in front of the kids because you feel uneasy, right?

157
00:12:02,250 --> 00:12:04,610
I find you a bit pitiful.

158
00:12:04,610 --> 00:12:09,630
Right now, even though you're doing great, it still feels like you are being chased.

159
00:12:11,740 --> 00:12:15,190
Oh, and stop eating that candy.

160
00:12:15,190 --> 00:12:17,270
Your teeth will rot.

161
00:12:18,620 --> 00:12:20,580
Lee Gil Yong.

162
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:22,410
Huh?

163
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:27,700
I heard. You're running away?

164
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:31,250
As if! I'm about to challenge myself.

165
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:34,790
In the past, because people had expectations,

166
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:38,800
because it was my parents' wish, I did run away.

167
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:44,190
But now, I want to prove it to myself and become a better person.

168
00:12:44,190 --> 00:12:46,450
I will take the GED exam and go to college too.

169
00:12:46,450 --> 00:12:50,780
In this world, there is not only one correct answer.

170
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,890
Why?

171
00:12:55,890 --> 00:12:58,350
Oh, it's just...

172
00:12:58,350 --> 00:13:00,630
You're irritating.

173
00:13:02,220 --> 00:13:04,410
I'll call you.

174
00:13:18,770 --> 00:13:20,280
 GED Exam

175
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:24,540
Oh, Gil Yong! Are these yours? GED?

176
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:27,610
Yes, I quit school.

177
00:13:27,610 --> 00:13:30,530
What? Really?

178
00:13:30,530 --> 00:13:33,070
Are you okay?

179
00:13:33,070 --> 00:13:34,410
I'm okay.

180
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:39,160
From now, I'll think about the type of adult I want to become.

181
00:13:40,610 --> 00:13:45,520
Oh, that's right. I'm really sorry about suddenly canceling our movie plans.

182
00:13:45,520 --> 00:13:47,950
We can just watch one next time.

183
00:13:47,950 --> 00:13:50,960
You're going to bring that out, right? I'll do it.

184
00:13:50,960 --> 00:13:51,830
No, it's fine.

185
00:13:51,830 --> 00:13:54,420
No. I'll do it.

186
00:13:58,270 --> 00:14:02,390
Did something good happen? She's in a good mood.

187
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:06,360
Ah, when do I give her the gift?

188
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:16,580
You must be idle these days. We meet quite often.

189
00:14:16,580 --> 00:14:23,170
Moments when you can feel the time flow, it's very new.

190
00:14:23,170 --> 00:14:26,500
How does it feel to watch?

191
00:14:27,410 --> 00:14:30,630
I think it was logical.

192
00:14:30,630 --> 00:14:34,080
It is going to go away anyway.

193
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:37,910
So that logic dragged me to this point then?

194
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:40,200
I'm sick and tired of it.

195
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:44,830
That's why... you should start following reason now.

196
00:14:44,830 --> 00:14:46,600
The end result is obvious.

197
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:50,940
Must I... must I watch you die?

198
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:57,070
If I die, are you going to leave me a flower or what?

199
00:14:58,660 --> 00:15:01,960
Sorry, but I'll decline in advance.

200
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:09,730
 The Witch's Diner

201
00:15:18,420 --> 00:15:20,680
- Hello. 
 - Hello.

202
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:24,260
Is the owner inside?

203
00:15:29,570 --> 00:15:33,580
I steamed this and brought it right away for you all.

204
00:15:33,580 --> 00:15:35,570
It will be really delicious.

205
00:15:35,570 --> 00:15:37,800
- Thank you. 
 - Yes.

206
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:43,290
- How does it taste? 
 - Yum!

207
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:45,380
It's really good and smells nice too!

208
00:15:45,380 --> 00:15:47,360
It's all thanks to my son.

209
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:52,400
These days, my son... what's that... cli-cli...

210
00:15:52,400 --> 00:15:55,610
That thing, you know? Where you climb the wall.

211
00:15:55,610 --> 00:15:58,050
- Ah, climbing? 
- Yeah, that!

212
00:15:58,050 --> 00:16:00,220
Right, that. He's been into that recently.

213
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:05,660
He goes every day and picks up all the good things around the world.

214
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:09,840
However, how old are you this year, young lady?

215
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:13,040
I'm 28 years.

216
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,680
Ah, what a good time.

217
00:16:14,680 --> 00:16:17,990
It's the perfect age to get married.

218
00:16:17,990 --> 00:16:22,190
But are you seeing anyone now?

219
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:23,880
Why?

220
00:16:23,880 --> 00:16:26,880
My son is still a bachelor.

221
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,750
Really a bachelor!

222
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:33,200
I wish my son would get married soon.

223
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:36,090
Here, take a look.

224
00:16:36,090 --> 00:16:42,350
My son's visuals resemble me, so he's very handsome.

225
00:16:42,350 --> 00:16:46,870
In the past, he would be considered a real looker.

226
00:16:46,870 --> 00:16:47,850
Welcome.

227
00:16:47,850 --> 00:16:52,530
As a shop owner, he's kind and so well-behaved,

228
00:16:52,530 --> 00:16:55,980
just like a presidential commendation type.

229
00:16:55,980 --> 00:17:00,750
On top of that, he's unbelievably good at organizing.

230
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:04,710
Imagine how well he will treat his wife when he gets married.

231
00:17:06,060 --> 00:17:11,670
But my son has only one flaw.

232
00:17:11,670 --> 00:17:15,370
He's 50 years old.

233
00:17:15,370 --> 00:17:18,850
However age doesn't matter these days, right?

234
00:17:18,850 --> 00:17:21,220
Am I right?

235
00:17:21,220 --> 00:17:26,230
But... I'm seeing someone.

236
00:17:28,550 --> 00:17:30,530
Oh really? I see.

237
00:17:30,530 --> 00:17:33,780
Aigoo, then I spoke a lot of nonsense.

238
00:17:33,780 --> 00:17:37,420
When you become this old, you have no sense. None at all.

239
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:40,410
It's about time I leave now.

240
00:17:44,010 --> 00:17:46,900
No, no, no, no need to see me out.

241
00:17:46,900 --> 00:17:48,310
- Go back safety. 
 - Bye.

242
00:17:48,310 --> 00:17:50,970
Goodbye.

243
00:17:50,970 --> 00:17:53,730
She reminds me of my grandmother who passed away.

244
00:17:56,380 --> 00:17:58,850
- By the way, Noona... 
 - Yeah?

245
00:17:58,850 --> 00:18:02,530
- Are you see— 
 - What are you doing over there?

246
00:18:02,530 --> 00:18:05,830
The old landlady stopped by briefly.

247
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:14,940
 Notice

248
00:18:15,970 --> 00:18:19,630
Grandma, did you come to make a wish?

249
00:18:22,180 --> 00:18:29,000
 Any wish is possible.  The effect is certain.

250
00:18:36,870 --> 00:18:40,590
That grandma earlier was interested in Noona.

251
00:18:40,590 --> 00:18:42,520
Would her son's marriage be her wish?

252
00:18:42,520 --> 00:18:44,560
But still, that's...

253
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:46,430
But there is nothing wrong with it either.

254
00:18:46,430 --> 00:18:50,730
Still, that ahjussi and Noona are not right for each other. Their age difference is too much.

255
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:54,030
What does love have to do with the age difference?

256
00:18:54,980 --> 00:18:57,260
That's right. It doesn't matter.

257
00:18:57,260 --> 00:19:02,520
But Noona said she is seeing someone else.

258
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:07,010
So that's where the problem lies.

259
00:19:08,020 --> 00:19:10,550
Witch, try these rice cakes out.

260
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:12,120
That grandma brought it.

261
00:19:12,120 --> 00:19:15,850
Rice-cake? I don't really like those.

