00:26:47,670 --> 00:26:49,870
I would even give my liver.

359
00:26:49,870 --> 00:26:52,060
Your liver? I don't need it.

360
00:26:52,060 --> 00:26:54,040
It's very old so I can't use it.

361
00:26:54,040 --> 00:26:56,200
Is that so?

362
00:26:58,040 --> 00:27:03,950
Then, what should I give you?

363
00:27:14,530 --> 00:27:16,810
You find the recipe.

364
00:27:16,810 --> 00:27:19,440
What? I should?

365
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:22,800
You are different from me, right? You even worry about the grandmother.

366
00:27:22,800 --> 00:27:26,700
So find something that is suitable for her.

367
00:27:27,990 --> 00:27:30,560
How would I know what recipe to find?

368
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:34,740
The mindset we have when cooking is the most important part.

369
00:27:42,180 --> 00:27:44,140
Actually,

370
00:27:45,560 --> 00:27:49,750
I'm a bit scared.

